---
import DocsLayout from "../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro";
---

<DocsLayout
  title="Semantic graph · Squeezy"
  description="How Squeezy builds and refreshes graph-backed static analysis for code navigation."
  activeDoc="/docs/semantic-navigation/"
  eyebrow="semantic graph"
  heading="Squeezy builds a local map before it asks the model to reason."
  lead="The graph is the main cost-control mechanism: it turns broad repository questions into narrowed local answers with paths, spans, and confidence."
>
  <section class="doc-block">
    <h2>What the graph stores</h2>
    <div class="doc-card-grid">
      <article class="card">
        <span class="label">symbols</span>
        <h3>Declarations and definitions</h3>
        <p>Functions, methods, types, modules, imports, fields, tests, and language-specific declaration forms are indexed by supported parser families.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="card">
        <span class="label">edges</span>
        <h3>References and relationships</h3>
        <p>The graph records references, call candidates, hierarchy, imports, inheritance, implements edges, and flow-style relationships where the language support can infer them locally.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="card">
        <span class="label">facts</span>
        <h3>Workspace context</h3>
        <p>Bounded workspace facts are attached where implemented so navigation can use project structure instead of treating every file as isolated text.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="card">
        <span class="label">labels</span>
        <h3>Confidence and freshness</h3>
        <p>Results carry provenance, source hashes, freshness, and confidence labels so the agent can route from graph facts to exact source slices.</p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="doc-block">
    <h2>Refresh behavior</h2>
    <p>Squeezy keeps an in-memory query surface backed by persisted graph/cache partitions. The graph can hydrate lazily and refresh changed files as the workspace changes, so long sessions can reuse graph state efficiently.</p>
    <pre><code>repo_map
decl_search
definition_search
reference_search
symbol_context
hierarchy
upstream_flow
downstream_flow
read_slice</code></pre>
  </section>

  <section class="doc-block">
    <h2>Coverage labels guide the next action</h2>
    <p>Generated files, vendor paths, dynamic language features, framework conventions, and external packages stay visible in the result with labels that tell the agent whether to continue with graph navigation, read an exact slice, search locally, or run a verifier.</p>
  </section>
</DocsLayout>
